{"id": "duc04-testb-39:13#41", "contents": "The situation is becoming increasingly complex, with many Republicans trying to navigate their loyalty to Gingrich while also considering the possibility of a new speaker. Rep. Peter King reported that Livingston told him he had received a very positive response about running for speaker and would decide within the next 48 hours. However, an aide to a Republican noted that many people are still loyal to Gingrich, and Livingston will only make a move if he has enough support. The outcome of the secret ballot on November 18 will be crucial in determining the future of the House leadership."}
